cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new algorithm for multi-label active learning based on Maximum Correntropy Criterion (MCC) to reduce label costs and improve the ability to train a good model. It also involves merging uncertainty and representativeness to enhance the similarity measurement of multi-label data with labels information. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper involves developing a new algorithm for active learning, cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as multi-label learning is commonly used in these fields, and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper proposes an efficient alternating optimization method to solve the algorithm.
